channel.title: Azure AI Foundry Model Updates
channel.description: Latest updates on Azure AI Foundry models sold directly by Azure

item.title: gpt-5.2-codex
item.description: A GPT-5.2 series reasoning model optimized for developer coding workflows, including Codex CLI and the Codex VS Code extension. It supports text and image processing plus structured outputs and advanced tool/function calling.

item.title: gpt-5.2
item.description: A GPT-5.2 series reasoning model with support for both Chat Completions and Responses APIs. It supports structured outputs, multimodal (text/image) input, and function/tool calling including parallel tool calling.

item.title: gpt-5.2-chat
item.description: A GPT-5.2 chat model in preview intended for conversational use via Chat Completions and Responses APIs. It supports structured outputs and function/tool calling with a smaller context window than the main gpt-5.2 model.

item.title: gpt-5.1
item.description: A GPT-5.1 series reasoning model supporting Chat Completions and Responses APIs with multimodal (text/image) input. It includes structured outputs and function/tool calling with parallel tool calling.

item.title: gpt-5.1-chat
item.description: A GPT-5.1 chat model in preview that adds built-in reasoning capabilities for conversational scenarios. It supports structured outputs and tool/function calling, but (as a reasoning model) does not support parameters like temperature.

item.title: gpt-5.1-codex
item.description: A GPT-5.1 Codex-optimized model available via the Responses API only. It supports text and image processing, structured outputs, and advanced tool/function calling for coding workflows.

item.title: gpt-5.1-codex-mini
item.description: A smaller GPT-5.1 Codex-optimized model available via the Responses API only. It supports multimodal input, structured outputs, and tool/function calling for coding and automation tasks.

item.title: gpt-5.1-codex-max
item.description: A GPT-5.1 Codex-optimized model (Responses API only) designed for higher reasoning capability. It adds support for setting reasoning_effort to xhigh, and does not support reasoning_effort=none.

item.title: gpt-5
item.description: A GPT-5 series reasoning model supporting Chat Completions and Responses APIs. It supports structured outputs, multimodal (text/image) input, and function/tool calling including parallel tool calling.

item.title: gpt-5-mini
item.description: A smaller GPT-5 reasoning model offering the same core API surface (Chat Completions and Responses) and capabilities like structured outputs and tool/function calling. It supports text and image processing with a large context window.

item.title: gpt-5-nano
item.description: A compact GPT-5 reasoning model intended for cost/latency-sensitive scenarios while retaining structured outputs and tool/function calling. It supports multimodal input and large-context reasoning via Chat Completions and Responses APIs.

item.title: gpt-5-chat
item.description: A GPT-5 chat model in preview for conversational use with text/image input and text output. A newer preview version (2025-10-03) adds enhancements focused on emotional intelligence and mental health conversations.

item.title: gpt-5-codex
item.description: A GPT-5 Codex-optimized model available via the Responses API only, designed for coding and agentic tooling workflows. It supports structured outputs, multimodal input, and advanced tool/function calling including parallel tool calling.

item.title: gpt-5-pro
item.description: A GPT-5 reasoning model intended for higher capability, available via the Responses API. It supports structured outputs, multimodal input, and function/tool calling.

item.title: gpt-oss-120b
item.description: An open-weight reasoning model (preview) for text-in/text-out chat scenarios. It supports streaming, function calling, and structured outputs, and can be deployed (requires a Foundry project) or used via managed compute.

item.title: gpt-oss-20b
item.description: A smaller open-weight reasoning model (preview) for text-in/text-out chat. It supports streaming, function calling, and structured outputs, and is available via managed compute and Foundry Local.

item.title: gpt-4.1
item.description: A GPT-4.1 series multimodal model supporting text and image input with text output. It supports Chat Completions and Responses APIs, streaming, function calling, and structured outputs (Chat Completions).

item.title: gpt-4.1-mini
item.description: A smaller GPT-4.1 series multimodal model with text and image input and text output. It supports Chat Completions and Responses APIs, streaming, function calling, and structured outputs (Chat Completions).

item.title: gpt-4.1-nano
item.description: A compact GPT-4.1 series multimodal model supporting text and image input with text output. It supports Chat Completions and Responses APIs, streaming, function calling, and structured outputs (Chat Completions).

item.title: computer-use-preview
item.description: An experimental preview model trained for use with the Responses API computer use tool. It can control mouse/keyboard via third-party libraries and uses screenshots as image input for environment context.

item.title: codex-mini
item.description: An o-series model that is a fine-tuned version of o4-mini, optimized for coding-style reasoning and tool use. It is available via the Responses API and supports structured outputs, multimodal processing, and functions/tools.

item.title: o3-pro
item.description: An advanced o-series reasoning model designed for high-focus problem solving in areas like science, coding, and math. It supports the Responses API with structured outputs, multimodal processing, and functions/tools.

item.title: o4-mini
item.description: A newer o-series reasoning model offering enhanced reasoning abilities compared to prior iterations. It supports both Chat Completions and Responses APIs, structured outputs, multimodal processing, and functions/tools.

item.title: o3
item.description: A newer o-series reasoning model with enhanced reasoning abilities and support for parallel tool calling. It supports Chat Completions and Responses APIs, structured outputs, and multimodal text/image processing.

item.title: o3-mini
item.description: A smaller o-series reasoning model focused on text-only processing with structured outputs and tool/function support. It targets reasoning tasks with a large request budget while remaining lighter than larger o-series models.

item.title: o1
item.description: An o-series reasoning model supporting structured outputs, multimodal (text/image) processing, and functions/tools. It is designed for advanced reasoning and problem-solving tasks with increased focus.

item.title: o1-preview
item.description: An older preview version in the o1 series. It is only available to customers who were granted access as part of the original limited access release.

item.title: o1-mini
item.description: A faster and more cost-efficient o1-series option, positioned as ideal for coding tasks requiring speed and lower resource consumption. Global Standard deployment is available by default, while standard (regional) deployments are limited to select customers from the o1-preview limited access release.

item.title: gpt-4o
item.description: A multimodal GPT-4o (Omni) model that accepts text and images and supports structured outputs, JSON mode, and parallel function calling. It is positioned as matching GPT-4 Turbo in English/coding while improving non-English and vision performance, with multiple dated versions available.

item.title: gpt-4o-mini
item.description: A fast, inexpensive multimodal model intended as a capable replacement for GPT-3.5 Turbo series models. It supports text and image processing, JSON mode, and parallel function calling.

item.title: gpt-4 (turbo-2024-04-09)
item.description: GPT-4 Turbo with Vision is a generally available model used with the Chat Completions API. It replaces previous GPT-4 preview models (vision-preview, 1106-Preview, 0125-Preview), with feature availability varying by input method and deployment type.

item.title: text-embedding-3-large
item.description: The latest and most capable embedding model for converting text into vectors for similarity and retrieval. It supports a dimensions parameter to reduce embedding size for cost/performance control, and migration from older models requires regenerating embeddings.

item.title: text-embedding-3-small
item.description: A third-generation embedding model for text-to-vector conversion with improved multilingual retrieval performance over older embeddings. It supports reducing embedding size via a dimensions parameter (depending on client library support).

item.title: text-embedding-ada-002
item.description: A legacy embedding model (versions 1 and 2) for converting text into 1,536-dimensional vectors. The documentation notes you cannot upgrade between embedding models; moving to text-embedding-3-large requires generating new embeddings.

item.title: gpt-image-1
item.description: A GPT-image-1 series image generation model in limited access preview that generates images from text prompts (and is described as part of limited access preview). Access requires registration and deployment creation after approval.

item.title: gpt-image-1-mini
item.description: A smaller GPT-image-1 series image generation model in limited access preview. Access requires registration, and it is available in multiple Global Standard regions listed in the documentation.

item.title: gpt-image-1.5
item.description: A GPT-image-1 series image generation model in limited access preview. Access requires registration and is available in several Global Standard regions (for example West US 3, East US 2, UAE North, Poland Central, Sweden Central).

item.title: dall-e-3
item.description: An image generation model that creates images from natural language prompts. It is generally available for use with the REST APIs, with regional availability including East US, Australia East, and Sweden Central.

item.title: sora
item.description: An OpenAI video generation model that can create realistic and imaginative video scenes from text instructions. It is in preview and available in East US 2 and Sweden Central (Global Standard).

item.title: sora-2
item.description: A newer Sora video generation model listed as NEW and in preview. It is available in East US 2 and Sweden Central (Global Standard).

item.title: gpt-4o-mini-audio-preview
item.description: A GPT-4o family preview audio model for audio and text generation. It supports large token requests and is intended for audio-enabled generation scenarios.

item.title: gpt-4o-audio-preview
item.description: A GPT-4o family preview audio model for audio and text generation. It supports large token requests and is part of the GPT-4o audio model family.

item.title: gpt-4o-realtime-preview
item.description: A GPT-4o family preview model for real-time audio processing. Multiple dated versions are listed, indicating iterative updates while remaining in preview.

item.title: gpt-4o-mini-realtime-preview
item.description: A GPT-4o mini family preview model for real-time audio processing. It is designed for low-latency conversational interactions with speech input/output.

item.title: gpt-realtime
item.description: A generally available (GA) audio model for real-time audio processing. It is listed alongside related realtime and audio variants and is intended for low-latency audio interactions.

item.title: gpt-realtime-mini
item.description: A smaller realtime audio model variant intended for real-time audio processing. Multiple versions are listed (including a 2025-12-15 variant), indicating ongoing updates.

item.title: gpt-realtime-mini-2025-12-15
item.description: A specific dated version of the gpt-realtime-mini model. It is part of the realtime audio model line for low-latency audio processing.

item.title: gpt-audio
item.description: An audio model listed for real-time audio processing use cases. It is part of the Azure OpenAI audio model lineup accessible via realtime/completions/audio APIs.

item.title: gpt-audio-mini
item.description: A smaller audio model variant intended for real-time audio processing. Multiple versions are listed (including a 2025-12-15 variant), indicating iterative updates.

item.title: whisper
item.description: A general-purpose speech recognition model used for speech-to-text and also listed for speech translation. It supports audio file uploads up to 25 MB via the Audio API.

item.title: gpt-4o-transcribe
item.description: A speech-to-text model powered by GPT-4o for transcription via the Audio API. It supports audio file uploads up to 25 MB.

item.title: gpt-4o-mini-transcribe
item.description: A speech-to-text model powered by GPT-4o mini for transcription via the Audio API. It supports audio file uploads up to 25 MB.

item.title: gpt-4o-transcribe-diarize
item.description: A speech-to-text model that adds diarization/automatic speech recognition capabilities. It supports audio file uploads up to 25 MB and is listed with a dated version in the model availability tables.

item.title: gpt-4o-mini-transcribe-2025-12-15
item.description: A dated speech-to-text model variant with improved transcription accuracy and robustness. It supports audio file uploads up to 25 MB via the Audio API.

item.title: tts
item.description: A preview text-to-speech model optimized for speed. It is available via the Audio API for generating speech from text.

item.title: tts-hd
item.description: A preview text-to-speech model optimized for quality. It is available via the Audio API for higher-fidelity speech generation from text.

item.title: gpt-4o-mini-tts
item.description: A preview text-to-speech model powered by GPT-4o mini that supports guiding the voice style or tone. It is available via the Audio API and appears with multiple dated versions in availability tables.

item.title: gpt-4o-mini-tts-2025-12-15
item.description: A dated version of the GPT-4o mini text-to-speech model (preview). It supports guiding the voice to speak in a specific style or tone via the Audio API.

item.title: model-router
item.description: A Microsoft model that routes requests across underlying models to match capability and context needs, supporting text and image input with text output. Multiple versions are available (including 2025-11-18, 2025-08-07, and 2025-05-19), and output limits vary based on the routed model.

item.title: o3-deep-research
item.description: A specialized o-series model variant intended for deep research workflows. It is currently only available with Foundry Agent Service according to the model availability notes.

item.title: FLUX.2-pro
item.description: A Black Forest Labs image generation and editing model that supports both text and image prompts, including multi-reference input (up to 8 images via API). It returns a single image (PNG/JPG) and is available via the BFL service provider API in Global Standard across all regions.

item.title: FLUX.1-Kontext-pro
item.description: A Black Forest Labs in-context image generation/editing model focused on character consistency and advanced editing. It supports text+image input and is available via both the Image API endpoints and the BFL provider API, with Global Standard availability in all regions.

item.title: FLUX-1.1-pro
item.description: A Black Forest Labs text-to-image model emphasizing fast inference speed, strong prompt adherence, and scalable generation. It is available via the Image API and the BFL provider API, with Global Standard availability in all regions.

item.title: Cohere-rerank-v4.0-pro
item.description: A Cohere rerank/text-classification model for ranking and relevance scoring over text inputs. It returns JSON output and is available in Global Standard across all regions, including via managed compute.

item.title: Cohere-rerank-v4.0-fast
item.description: A faster Cohere rerank/text-classification model for text relevance ranking. It returns JSON output and is available in Global Standard across all regions, including via managed compute.

item.title: Cohere-command-a
item.description: A Cohere chat-completion model optimized for use cases like reasoning, summarization, and question answering. It supports tool calling and can return either text or JSON, with Global Standard availability in all regions.

item.title: embed-v-4-0
item.description: A Cohere embeddings model that can embed both text and images into vectors with selectable dimensionality. It is available in Global Standard across all regions and supports multiple languages.

item.title: DeepSeek-V3.2-Speciale
item.description: A DeepSeek chat-completion model that includes reasoning content and is optimized for step-by-step reasoning tasks. It supports text input/output with large token limits and is available in Global Standard across all regions.

item.title: DeepSeek-V3.2
item.description: A DeepSeek chat-completion model with reasoning content designed for language, scientific reasoning, and coding tasks. It supports large text input/output and is available in Global Standard across all regions.

item.title: DeepSeek-V3.1
item.description: A DeepSeek chat-completion model with reasoning content that supports tool calling. It is available in Global Standard across all regions and supports English and Chinese.

item.title: DeepSeek-R1-0528
item.description: A DeepSeek reasoning chat-completion model with very large input/output token limits. It is available in both Global Standard and Global Provisioned managed deployments across all regions.

item.title: DeepSeek-V3-0324
item.description: A DeepSeek chat-completion model (without the explicit 'reasoning content' label) that supports tool calling and JSON/text outputs. It is available in Global Standard and Global Provisioned managed deployments across all regions.

item.title: DeepSeek-R1
item.description: A DeepSeek reasoning chat-completion model with very large input/output token limits. It is available in Global Standard and Global Provisioned managed deployments across all regions.

item.title: Llama-4-Maverick-17B-128E-Instruct-FP8
item.description: A Meta multimodal chat-completion model that accepts text and images with an extremely large context window. It is available in Global Standard across all regions and returns text output.

item.title: Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct
item.description: A Meta chat-completion model for instruction-following text generation with a large context window. It is available in Global Standard across all regions and returns text output.

item.title: MAI-DS-R1
item.description: A Microsoft chat-completion model with reasoning content and very large input/output token limits. It is available in Global Standard across all regions.

item.title: Mistral-Large-3
item.description: A Mistral multimodal chat-completion model supporting text and image input with tool calling and JSON/text outputs. It is available in Global Standard in West US 3.

item.title: mistral-document-ai-2505
item.description: A Mistral Image-to-Text model for extracting text from images or PDF pages (up to 30 pages / 30MB). It returns text/JSON/Markdown and is available in Global Standard across all regions and Data Zone Standard in the US and EU.

item.title: Kimi-K2.5
item.description: A Moonshot AI multimodal reasoning model that accepts text and image input and returns text output with reasoning content. It supports tool calling and is available in Global Standard across all regions.

item.title: Kimi-K2-Thinking
item.description: A Moonshot AI reasoning model described as the latest and most capable open-source thinking model in this lineup. It supports tool calling and is available in Global Standard across all regions.

item.title: grok-4
item.description: An xAI Grok chat-completion model designed for enterprise use cases such as extraction, coding, summarization, and agentic applications. It supports tool calling and is available in Global Standard across all regions, with registration required for access.

item.title: grok-4-fast-reasoning
item.description: A Grok chat-completion model variant optimized for faster reasoning with text and image input. It supports tool calling and is available in Global Standard across all regions and Data Zone Standard in the US.

item.title: grok-4-fast-non-reasoning
item.description: A Grok chat-completion model variant optimized for faster non-reasoning scenarios with text and image input. It supports tool calling and is available in Global Standard across all regions and Data Zone Standard in the US.

item.title: grok-code-fast-1
item.description: A Grok chat-completion model optimized for coding-focused workloads. It supports tool calling and is available in Global Standard across all regions, with registration required for access.

item.title: grok-3
item.description: A Grok chat-completion model supporting tool calling with very large input/output token limits. It is available in Global Standard across all regions and Data Zone Standard in the US.

item.title: grok-3-mini
item.description: A smaller Grok chat-completion model supporting tool calling with very large input/output token limits. It is available in Global Standard across all regions and Data Zone Standard in the US.

item.title: Ministral-3B (preview) (2411)
item.description: A Mistral fine-tuning model listed as preview with unknown output and training example context length details in the fine-tuning table. It is not supported for standard regional fine-tuning, but is listed as available for global training.

item.title: Qwen-32B (preview)
item.description: A preview fine-tuning model listed with an 8,000 token input and 32,000 token output limit in the fine-tuning table. It is not supported for standard regional fine-tuning, but is listed as available for global training.

item.title: gpt-4
item.description: A GPT-4 model family referenced in Assistants and provisioned deployment availability tables with multiple versions (for example 0613, 1106-Preview, 0125-Preview). These models are used with the Chat Completions API and have region- and deployment-type-specific availability.

item.title: gpt-4-32k
item.description: A GPT-4 extended-context variant referenced in the Assistants and provisioned deployment availability tables (for example version 0613). Availability varies by region and deployment type as shown in the tables.

item.title: gpt-35-turbo
item.description: A GPT-3.5 Turbo family model referenced in Assistants and provisioned deployment availability tables (including versions like 0613, 1106, 0125, and a 16k variant). Availability varies by region and deployment type as shown in the tables.

item.title: gpt-35-turbo-16k
item.description: A GPT-3.5 Turbo extended-context variant referenced in the Assistants availability table (for example version 0613). It is available only in certain regions for Assistants, as shown in the documentation tables.
